
[1]scarlet

   SC'ARLET, n.

   1. A beautiful bright red color, brighter than crimson.

   2. Cloth of a scarlet color.

   All her household are clothed with scarlet. Prov. 31.

    SC'ARLET, a. of the color called scarlet; of a bright red color; as a
                   scarlet cloth or thread; a scarlet lip.
